The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of random ferns and energy minimization frameworks suggests a machine learning approach (cs.MM) and optimization techniques (cs.LG). The study of cellular mechanisms also suggests a biological aspect, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or information retrieval (cs.IR) if the focus is on analyzing and extracting information from the images.
